pr_body:
This commit tries to have certain css variable that will hold the general
most used colors of Zulip. They can be easily set at the top of the night
mode css file and this will reduce the overwriting of css properties.

One great feature of this PR that I liked is, if someone is designing something, it can happen that he just write the light theme css, and variables will automatically handle the color in dark theme.

For right now the first version of this task, I have created the following variables
```CSS
--color-background: hsl(0, 0%, 100%);
--color-background-highlight: hsl(0, 0%, 88%);
--color-background-modal: hsl(0, 0%, 98%);
--color-placeholder: hsl(0, 0%, 45%);
--color-hotspot-before: hsl(0, 0%, 80%);
--color-text: hsl(0, 0%, 0%);
```

<!-- What's this PR for?  (Just a link to an issue is fine.) -->
Link to [CZO here](https://chat.zulip.org/#narrow/stream/6-frontend/topic/variables.20in.20scss/near/1184419)

**Testing plan:** <!-- How have you tested? -->
Have tested the elements from which I remove the property and added the css.

